Great Bag












Verified Purchase


Terrific travel bag to go with in the cabin of the plane. Good room, outside pockets, and tie down straps in side.
Read More 






Good quality bag with maximized space












I got this bag 2 years bag with the intention of maximizing space to carry the bag on-board without checking-in. It has been 2 years of no regrets. The build is sturdy to throw around especially the 2 carrying handles.

However, i am suspicious of the shoulder strap- this is easily fixed with a hack of running another strap through the bottom of the bag so that the strap supports the entire weight of the bag. Now the only hack i need to do is for the backpack straps. 

I bring along a tiny foldable trolley which i keep inside the bag when i travel so that i can use it if i get too tired. Of course the bag flips over if you pack unevenly.

Really happy with it!!
Read More 






Easy Travel












Verified Purchase


We bought 2 of these bags for a trip to Europe and used them as our only luggage. I was able to put 30 lbs of things in mine and carry it everywhere. The bag is great and was the best bag we could find for the price.
Read More 






Great Carry-on!












Verified Purchase


We bought this bag to use for a carry on for a trip to Mexico.  I had no trouble packing in enough clothes for 2 weeks, and had room to bring quite a few souvenirs home thanks to the expandable zipper.  The large front pocket made it easy to pull out my zip-lock bag of toiletries for security inspection and pop it back in quickly.  Having so many zippered compartments made it easy to organize.  The straps were comfortable for backpacking it, though I didn't have to carry my luggage very far, just through busy airports.  I would recommend this bag to anyone who wants to travel light.  The only downside is that it is so roomy that you might be tempted to over pack!
Read More 






Love it












Verified Purchase


Ordered the bag for a trip to Europe after reading lots of reviews from different web sites. The bag arrived within a week and looks great. Lots of pockets and well-thought-out design. My husband wants one now...I may give him my "spruce" one and order the copper color, but the spruce is very nice.
Read More 






perfect!












Verified Purchase


After an airline lost my checked bag, I vowed only to take carry-on for flights. I bought Rick Steves carry-on bag for a week-long trip across the country, and it was perfect! Everything I needed fit; it complied with regulations and fit in overhead bins; and I love that you can carry it three ways. Also, all the zippered compartments are useful, and the fact that it doesn't have wheels makes it lighter and easier to fit (smash!) into smaller spaces.I highly recommend it!
Read More 






Ready to travel....












Verified Purchase


This Rick Steves bag is just what I was looking for.  Extremely well made with lots of pockets, zippers and extra features like hidden backpack straps and waist strap.  This will be my only piece of luggage for a 22-day trip to England.  Plenty of room for all that I need to take with me.
Read More 






Great bag












Verified Purchase


I had heard and read many good things about this bag and with an upcoming trip to Europe decided to order it.  It arrived very quickly and was exactly as represented.  It seems very sturdy and well made with attention to detail.  There are many pockets and lots of flexibility with this bag.  The color choices are nice and the compression straps are nice too.  If I had one hesitation, it would be that there are so many outside zippers that it is difficult to lock it on the outside.  It would require more than one lock to try to secure the contents of the pockets.  I would not want to lock it in every situation but in some places we will be traveling, having the ability to lock it would be a good and necessary thing.
Read More 






Excellent product












Verified Purchase


This is the second Rick Steves Convertible Carry-On I've purchased. My son liked his so much, that I got one for my daughter's first extended trip to Europe. My son is an aficionado of crazy amounts of hidden compartments, pockets, zippers, straps, etc., and this piece of luggage passed his muster with flying colors. It really is a practical and excellently made piece of luggage.
Read More 






So far so good












Verified Purchase


Just bought the bag to use for my airplane carry on for a week long vacation. Worked great, I didn't use the expansion zipper because of the size limitations, but even with the basic volume got everything I needed inside. Only thing is that the bag is a bit floppy - sags when not full so weight shifts around  a bit when its over your shoulder. But I like the fact there are  no wheels, the bag itself weighs almost nothing, and I liked the configuration of the   front pockets a lot. 
Didn't use it as a backpack, but used the waist straps to wrap around the front to cinch the bag tight.
