Good Stuff












Verified Purchase


Very heavy duty , thick fabric and well made zippers. I like the pocket set up as well. No regrets.
Read More 






Great Bag












This is a great bag for the casual traveler. It is very well made with quality materials and it is as or more durable than many packs/bags costing much more. The pockets are well designed and the entire bag is well thought out. Like all of the Rick Steves products I have purchased over the years, I am very happy with this bag. It has been to Europe quite a few times with me and still looks like new. I sometimes check the bag and sometimes it's a carry-on (depending one how much I am carrying and the airline), with absolutely no problems with the conveyor systems.While I don't believe that this pack is a substitute for a dedicated internal or external frame pack for serious or professional trekkers or climbers, Rick does not purport it to be that. There is no actual frame and the shoulder straps and waist straps don't transfer weight like some of the more expensive ($250+) packs. However, those packs don't have the versatility of this Rick Steves pack/bag. This bag has both vertical and horizontal hand grips; a separate shoulder strap is available; both the waist belt and shoulder straps are concealable; finally, it is a comfortable backpack with well-padded shoulder straps. All of that plus being both expandable and having cinch straps make the bag hard to beat. I usually carry about 25-35 lbs without difficulty and the pack is not full. Buy one.
Read More 






